    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Easily spin up a development server which launches in your browser. It watches for changes in your source files and automatically reloads with the updated build."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "By default, ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic serve"
      ],
      " boots up a development server on ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "localhost"
      ],
      ". To serve to your LAN, specify the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "--external"
      ],
      " option, which will use all network interfaces and print the external address(es) on which your app is being served."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Try the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "--lab"
      ],
      " option to see multiple platforms at once."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic serve"
      ],
      " uses the Angular CLI. Use ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ng serve --help"
      ],
      " to list all Angular CLI options for serving your app. See the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ng serve"
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://angular.io/cli/serve"
